parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to loss of traction control and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Intermittent or permanent illumination of the ABS warning light
vibration or pulsation when applying the brakes
and/or sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotor can cause the brake system to malfunction, leading to loss of braking power, increased stopping distance, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Abnormal sounds or vibrations when applying the brakes
and/or visible signs of brake rotor wear or damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air pump can cause the brake system to malfunction, leading to loss of braking power, increased stopping distance, and potential accidents.
symptoms: resulting in loss of brake assist
and/or increased effort required to apply the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the headlight switch can cause the headlights to go out while driving, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the headlight bulbs can cause reduced visibility while driving, leading to increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: bulbs need to be replaced multiple times
physical condition makes it difficult to change bulbs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signals can cause reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially when changing lanes or turning.
The placement of the hazard switch too close to the gear shift lever can cause accidental activation of the hazard lights, leading to confusion and potential accidents.
symptoms: Hazard switch is too close to the gear shift lever.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the timing belt and tensioner can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Flow Sensor and Mass Air Flow Sensor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the air flow sensor and mass air flow sensor can cause the engine to shut down, leading to loss of power, steering, and brakes, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle randomly shuts off while driving
engine shut-down with loss of power steering control
stalling at normal operating speed with resulting loss of power

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the exhaust system can cause carbon monoxide to leak into the vehicle, posing a health hazard to occupants, and can also cause fires.
symptoms: Black smoke belching out of the exhaust pipe
strong odor (sulphur?) on an intermittent basis
daily exhaust odor inside car when driver or passenger window is opened a little
foul exhaust (rotten egg) odor which enters the vehicle when the driver's side window is down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the muffler and tailpipe can cause burns to occupants, especially children, due to the exposed and hot surface.
symptoms: Child burned by muffler in rear of vehicle
child suffered 2nd degree burn on leg by coming into contact with the exhaust pipe tip
